THE TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE IS ABOUT A STORY OF A LIBRARY CUSTODIAN NAMED RAYMOND CLARK, WHO WORKED AT THE WASHINGTON HEIGHTS BRANCH, WHERE HE MOVED INTO THE TOP FLOOR APARTMENT WITH HIS WIFE AND SON RONALD.
RONALD HAD SPENT HIS CHILDHOOD PRACTICALLY LIVING INSIDE THE LIBRARY WHERE HIS FATHER WORKED.
RONALD GREW UP IN A VERY POOR FAMILY, WITH PARENTS WHO NEVER GRADUATED FROM HIGH SCHOOL, TO WHERE HIS FATHER WORKED AND SAVED FOR HIM TO GRADUATE FROM COLLEGE AND BECOME A UNIVERSITY PROFESSOR.
RONALD STATES THAT HAD HIS FATHER NOT INSTILLED IN HIM THE IMPORTANCE OF LIBRARY PARTICIPATION, RONALD WOULD HAVE ENDED UP BROKE AND NEEDING ASSISTANCE.
RONALD NOW LIVES THE LIFE HE IMAGINED AND ATTRIBUTES ALL OF HIS SUCCESS TO THE YEARS HE SPENT LIVING INSIDE THE LIBRARY.
